  "concepts": [
    {
      "title": "Properties of hydrogen peroxide",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Oxidising nature and Bleaching action:</strong></h3><p><strong>1. ${{\\mathbf{H}}_{\\mathbf{2}}}{{\\mathbf{O}}_{\\mathbf{2}}}$ as a bleaching agent:</strong></p><p>Due to its oxidizing nature, it acts as a bleaching agent.</p><p>$\\text{ Coloured material }+\\text{O}\\xrightarrow{{}}\\text{ Colourless}\\text{. }$</p><p>It bleaches materials like silk, hair, ivory, cotton, wool etc.</p><p><strong>2. Oxidizing nature</strong></p><p>(a) <img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>(b) A solution of chromic acid in sulphuric acid or acidified potassium dictiromate is oxidized to blue peroxide of chromium$\\left( \\text{Cr}{{\\text{O}}_{5}} \\right)$ which is unstable, however, it is soluble in ether and produces blue coloured solution.</p><p>${{\\text{K}}_{2}}\\text{C}{{\\text{r}}_{2}}{{\\text{O}}_{7}}+{{\\text{H}}_{2}}\\text{S}{{\\text{O}}_{4}}+4{{\\text{H}}_{2}}{{\\text{O}}_{2}}\\xrightarrow{{}}\\underset{\\text{Blue}}{\\mathop{2\\text{Cr}{{\\text{O}}_{5}}}}\\,+{{\\text{K}}_{2}}\\text{S}{{\\text{O}}_{4}}+5{{\\text{H}}_{2}}\\text{O}$</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p>",
      "position": 0,
      "qcConcept": "66a0dcb4c03b9dcaf1afe74d"
    }
  ],
